<TITLE> Depression weakens, causes rains </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 9 (bdnews24.com)  The depression formed over Barisal moved north and north-westward Tuesday morning to hover over Tangail, Mymensingh, Sirajganj and areas close by, met office said. The depression was reported to have been causing medium to heavy rains all over the country and weakening gradually, it said in a bulletin. A low travelling from the Myanamar coasts made a landfall Monday noon and turned into a land depression. Under its influence, the seas remained turbulent and the weathermen advised Chittagong, Cox's Bazaar and Mongla maritime ports to keep local cautionary signal three hoisted until further notice. All fishing boats and trawlers have been asked to cruise close to the coasts and be cautious. Samarandra Karmakar, director, Bangladesh Meteorological Department, told bdnews24.com that the entire country had been having rains due to the land depression and that the squally wet weather might improve in the afternoon. Naima Baten, a weather expert, told bdnews24.com that the land depression might move further north-westward overland, causing fluctuations in the wind pressures in the northern Bay area. She said the monsoons were still very active all over Bangladesh, especially in north Bay, causing squally winds to blow over the seaports. The bulletin said all six divisions were likely to experience temporary gusty to squally winds accompanied by rain and thunderstorm at places. Dhaka, Khulna, Barisal and Chittagong divisions may see heavy to torrential rainfalls and a slightly lower day temperature. bdnews24
